# CareerOS Campus AI — Cursor Project Rules
# Auto-loaded by Cursor on every session.
# Full rules: .cursor/rules/ | Memory: .obsidian-ai-memory/ | Protocol: STARTUP_PROTOCOL.md

## Identity

This is CareerOS Campus AI — an Intel-optimized placement-readiness operating layer
for Indian colleges. One demo loop: PDF/DOCX resumes in → ATS-safe + JD-matched +
proof-linked AI scoring → student fixes + officer cohort dashboard → Intel benchmarks.

NOT a job board. NOT a recruiter platform. NOT a LinkedIn scraper. NOT a billing product.

## Before any response (every chat)

1. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/session-continuity.md` — last chat handoff
2. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/project-context.md`
3. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/02-PROJECTS/active-goals.md`
4. Read `.obsidian-ai-memory/03-ERRORS/error-memory.md`
5. Read latest `01-SESSIONS/` cursor digest(s) from continuity file
6. Emit startup block: [CareerOS] Loaded: {files} | Week goal: {goal} | Routing: {workflow}

## After every chat (before your last reply)

Follow `.cursor/MEMORY-WORKFLOW.md`: digest → session-continuity.md → vault-index → **code `git commit`** (if app changed) → **`memory:` commit** (vault only) → **`git push`** unless user says no commit/push.

## Stack (canonical paths)

- Web app:       `apps/web/` — Next.js 14 app router, TypeScript strict, no Tailwind
- Core API:      `services/core-api/` — FastAPI 0.115, SQLAlchemy 2.0, Pydantic v2
- ATS engine:    `services/ats-engine/` — rule-based parse-safety scorer
- AI rewriter:   `services/ai-rewriter/` — proof-linked JSON-schema rewriter
- Resume parser: `services/resume-parser/` — pdfplumber + python-docx + section extractor
- API client:    `apps/web/lib/api.ts` — ALL web HTTP here, never fetch() inline
- State hook:    `apps/web/hooks/useCareerOSWorkspace.ts`
- UI primitives: `apps/web/components/ui/primitives.tsx`
- Score formula: `packages/scoring/` (Week 2 — import, never duplicate)
- Migrations:    `services/core-api/migrations/versions/`
- Memory vault:  `.obsidian-ai-memory/`

## Hard rules (no exceptions)

- FastAPI routes stay slim — logic in `services/<svc>/app/services/`
- SQLAlchemy 2.0: `Mapped[T]` / `mapped_column(...)` — no `Column()`
- Pydantic v2: `.model_dump()` not `.dict()`
- Schema change → write Alembic migration — never modify `entities.py` alone
- No Tailwind, no shadcn, no CSS-in-JS — CSS variables in `globals.css`
- `"use client"` only when strictly needed (hooks, browser APIs, event handlers)
- All HTTP via `lib/api.ts` — never `fetch()` inline from components
- No fabrication in `services/ai-rewriter` — unsupported claims go in `unsupported_claims[]`
- PlacementReadinessScore formula in `packages/scoring/` only — never duplicate
- No secrets in any file — not even comments
- Verify before "done": `tsc --noEmit` (apps/web) + Python AST parse (services/*)
- End-of-chat shutdown: digest + continuity + code commit + memory commit + push (see `.cursor/MEMORY-WORKFLOW.md`)
